summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganCreate a laminated brow look with e.l.f. Cosmetics' clear-drying Brow Laminating Gel. The flake and water-resistant formula delivers e.l.f.'s strongest hold yet to lock down your brow look without stiffness. Plus, the dual-ended applicator lets you precisely sculpt, shape, and set your brows.
details: DetailsBenefitsClear-drying brow gel with e.l.f.'s strongest hold yet, perfect for creating the look of laminated browsLightweight feel without any stiffnessDual-end applicator applies gel, then combs & sculpts browsWater-resistant & flake-resistant100% vegan & cruelty-free, e.l.f. is Leaping Bunny Certifiede.l.f. is proud to partner with Fair Trade USA & manufacture products in Fair Trade Certified facilities; look for the Fair Trade Certified seal on your e.l.f. productFormulated WithoutPhthalatesParabensNonylphenol ethoxylatesTriclosanTriclocarbanHydroquinoneItem 2622892How To UseUsing the precision spoolie, apply a small amount of gel onto clean, dry brows.Brush hairs back and forth to fully cover with product.Shape brows with the comb end, then gently press up and out into brows with the brush to set hairs in place for a laminated look.Use the Instant Lift Brow Pencil or Ultra-Precision Brow Pencil (both sold separately) to fill in sparse areas as needed.IngredientsAqua, Ceteareth-30, Glycerin, Acrylates Copolymer, Paraffin, Microcrystalline Wax, Butylene Glycol, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Paraffinum Liquidum, Euphorbia Cerifera Wax, Copernicia Cerifera Cera, PVP, Palmitic Acid, Stearic Acid, Alcohol, Phenoxyethanol, Polysorbate 80, Aminomethyl Propanol, Hydroxypropyl Methylcellulose, Xanthan Gum, Tocopheryl Acetate, Ethylhexylglycerin, Disodium EDTA, Hydrolyzed Wheat Protein, Hydrolyzed Soy Protein, Hydrolyzed Corn Protein, Sodium Chloride.Ingredients may change or vary from time to time. faceoff_positive.comments:
I tried the Elf 3-in-1 Applicator Brow Laminating Gel and I am really impressed by the longevity of the hold. Over 10 and a half hours later my eyebrows still look pristine! It applies very easily and I don't find any white bits as it dries nice and clear. I don't actually care for the laminated look so I used it to set my brows normally and I'm a fan. I did notice that less is more as it is very strong hold and quick drying so work in small sections and build up as needed the product.

I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_positive.headline: Nice strong hold

faceoff_negative.comments:
Initially when I got this I thought it was going to simply hold my brows in place, but when I used it I quickly discovered its for pressing + sticking your brows down. The final look just wasn't what I thought it would be, and that's okay! 

I will start off by saying, I live in a hot climate area and I'm sensitive to heat, so i tend to sweat more than average. I feel like for that reason alone, this may not be the product that suits my needs.

The consistency is like a glue stick, but not solid if that makes sense. It's thick, white and dries clear. In order for it to work well, you need to press it down to your skin and smooth your brows in the way you like them to be. 

If it's hot outside and you know you'll be outside for an extended time, maybe put something else over it to make sure you don't sweat it off. 

Overall, it DOES do what it says it'll do. I'm happy with the ingredients and the quality, I would absolutely buy this. I love E.L.F! 

I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_negative.headline: It works; but not for me!
